article.headline: Duquesne 59, Robert Morris 54
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- B.J. Monteiro scored 17 points to lead Duquesne to a 59-54 victory over Robert Morris on Saturday night. Damien Saunders added 10 points and 17 rebounds for the Dukes (7-3), who took a 55-54 lead on Monteiro's jumper with 1:25 left and held the Colonials (3-5) scoreless the rest of the way. There were nine lead changes, five in the final 8:18. The Dukes led 51-46 with 4:58 left before Robert Morris' Karon Abraham hit a 3-pointer to cut the lead to 51-49. Saunders scored on a layup for a 53-49 advantage with 3:30 left, but Mezie Nwigwe scored on a layup and Velton Jones hit a 3 to give Robert Morris a 54-53 lead with 1:57 left. Duquesne scored the final six points. Robert Morris shot 35.6 percent from the field (21-for-59), the ninth opponent the Dukes have held to less than 40 percent shooting. Abraham scored 18 and Jones added 12 for Robert Morris.
